Plot.
In the not too distant future in Orange County California, an undercover 
narcotics agent is known internally in the force only by his code name, 
Fred. His identity within can be kept secret as the scanning suit he dons 
hides his true identity. In reality, he is Bob Arctor. His assignment is 
to infiltrate a drug ring dealing in a hallucinogen known as Substance D, 
the ultimate goal to find the source of the drug. Arctor's own use of 
Substance D and moving within this drug world is making him lose his true 
identity, which includes a family life with two young daughters. As Fred, 
he is also assigned to monitor his own movements since one of Arctor's 
drug colleagues, James Barris, has come to the authorities to report 
Arctor's drug dealings, although Fred's superior, code named Hank, knows 
that Fred in his true identity is one of the people in the drug ring being 
monitored. But Hank and Hank's colleagues will do anything, even sacrifice 
Fred/Arctor, to achieve the ultimate goal of finding the source of 
Substance D.
